		<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn"><a href='http://tymkrs.tumblr.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Addie (w0ttv)</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	 	</div><!-- end .comment-author -->

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="http://hackaday.com/2013/09/23/guest-rant-ham-radio-hackers-paradise/comment-page-1/#comment-1064531">September 24, 2013 at 12:48 pm</a>
					</div><!-- end .comment-meta -->

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I go through the ARRL guide pretty much page by page in my blog.  It&#8217;s actually how I started learning about electronics from having 0 experience.  I didn&#8217;t even know what a resistor was when I first started reading the ham radio guide.  It starts: <a href="http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/post/2828011632/first-ham-lessons-o-de-day" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/post/2828011632/first-ham-lessons-o-de-day</a> and you&#8217;ll see subsequent lessons in <a href="http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/archive/2011/2" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/archive/2011/2</a></p>
