	<li class="comment even depth-2 highlander-comment" id="comment-1063655">

		
		<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Justin</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	 	</div><!-- end .comment-author -->

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="http://hackaday.com/2013/09/23/guest-rant-ham-radio-hackers-paradise/comment-page-1/#comment-1063655">September 23, 2013 at 10:47 am</a>
					</div><!-- end .comment-meta -->

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>In the United States there is a 35 question test that gives you privileges on the bands.  There is a published question pool and you only need 75% correct to pass the test.  It constitutes mostly of the rules governing the use of the radios and is relatively easy.<br />
I highly recommend the Ham Radio License Manual which can be found on amazon or at the local library.</p>
		</div><!-- end .comment-content -->

