					</div><!-- end .comment-meta -->

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I was a CB brat back in the late 60&#8242;s. Big deal then was running a ham rig that you converted to work on 11 meters(CB band). Thats where I got bit by the bug. I bought &amp; built a Heathkit station &amp; converted it. I still have that gear! Never could master Morse code. Now I finally got my &#8216;ticket&#8217; that code is no longer required. It is a great, rewarding hobby. I highly recommend it. W2RNJ</p>
