					</div><!-- end .comment-meta -->

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Oh, and not to forget: being a HAM ain&#8217;t that bad in job interviews, either. I am working as a software engineer (embedded) and all my employers either were HAMs themselves or did understand the meaning. Being able to state my call-sign (DG9FAB,btw) always gave me the credibility that I could touch a soldering iron w/o hurting myself. Maybe that&#8217;s one day the thing that distinguishes you from the other applicants&#8230;</p>
